I think a main wallet giving an app an "allowance" could be nice. So you don't have to deep link into a wallet to confirm every single tx.

E.g. I love the frame tx flow but the Warpcast confirmation pane should be the one and only step in the checkout process.

The deep link, CB wallet boot up, waiting for confirmation to load, hitting confirm, deep linking back to Warpcast, needs to be cut.

I think session key could be nice. CB wallet still does the heavy lifting, but you configure it once via deep link and then drive it with Warpcast after, cutting all the extra steps. Maybe one in a while you top off or permit more funds in CB wallet via deep link.

Warpcast shouldn't have to build a full wallet.
